==English==
===Etymology===
From late Latin ''superpelliceum'', from ''super'' (over) and ''pellis'' (fur).
===Noun===
'''surplice'''
#A [[liturgical]] [[vestment]] of the Christian Church. It has the form of a [[tunic]] of white [[linen]] or [[cotton]] material, with wide or moderately wide sleeves, reaching to the hips or knees. It usually features lace decoration and may have embroidered [[bordure]]s.

